14. Interview Questions Related to Pop
What does pop() return?
What happens if you pop from an empty stack?
What is the time complexity of pop()?
Why is pop() an O(1) operation?
How is pop() implemented in an array?
How is pop() implemented in a linked list?
15. One Analogy to Remember Everything

Imagine a stack of books.

Top
 ↓
Java
Python
C++

You can only remove the Java book first.

pop()

Result

Top
 ↓
Python
C++

You cannot directly remove C++ because Java and Python are above it.

This is why a stack follows LIFO (Last In, First Out).

⭐ Quick Revision (30 Seconds)
Pop = Remove the top element from the stack.
Returns the removed element.
Works only on the top-most element.
Follows LIFO (Last In, First Out).
Time Complexity = O(1).
On an empty stack → Underflow (EmptyStackException in Java).
Always use isEmpty() before pop() if the stack might be empty.
